1. insert install dvd.

2. boot to dvd.

3. Select language. Hit next.

4. Bottom left corner, repair computer

5. Troubleshoot  (for Windows 8 and 8.1, you then need to select Advanced options)

6. Command prompt

7. cd /d c:\windows\system32

8. move utilman.exe utilman.exe.bak

9. copy cmd.exe utilman.exe

10. shutdown /r /t 0 /f

11. Select the Ease of Access tool in the bottom left(circlish looking thing).

12. net user administrator *

*note* this is for the case where administrator is the superuser. You may have to run net user to get a list of users, then net user X to find the admin.

13. Enter in new password.

14. Close the command prompt and login.

And if for some reason that fails, use something to blank the password:

with ISO

http://pogostick.net/~pnh/ntpasswd/

To put onto a flash drive

http://unetbootin.sourceforge.net/

source: http://www.howtogeek.com/106333/how-to-reset-your-forgotten-domain-admin-password-on-server-2008-r2/
